This article discusses President Biden's decision to suspend tariffs on steel imports from Ukraine for a period of one year. The decision comes in light of the ongoing security discussions between the United States and Ukraine, as well as the significant disruption in Ukraine's steel industry caused by the war with Russia. The suspension is aimed at supporting Ukraine's recovery and maintaining its steel industry as an economic lifeline. The Secretary of Commerce will monitor the situation and provide updates to the President as necessary. The article also mentions that the current tariff level on steel imports from other countries will be maintained for now. The proclamation cites the authority vested in the President by various trade acts and declares the adjustments to the duty rate on steel imports.